        "type": "element",
        "tag": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "em",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The warforged were built to fight in the Last War. The first warforged were mindless automatons, but House Cannith devoted vast resources to improving these steel soldiers. An unexpected breakthrough produced fully sentient soldiers, blending organic and inorganic materials. Warforged are made from wood and metal, but they can feel pain and emotion. Built as weapons, they must now find a purpose beyond the war. A warforged can be a steadfast ally, a cold-hearted killing machine, or a visionary in search of purpose and meaning."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "h1",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eberron - Rising from the Last War"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ability Score Increase."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Your Constitution score increases by 2, and one other ability score of your choice increases by 1."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Age."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " A typical warforged is between two and thirty years old. The maximum lifespan of the warforged remains a mystery; so far, warforged have shown no signs of deterioration due to age. You are immune to magical aging effects."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Alignment."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Most warforged take comfort in order and discipline, tending toward law and neutrality. But some have absorbed the morality – or lack thereof – of the beings with which they served."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Size."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Your size is Medium. To set your height and weight randomly, start with rolling a size modifier. "
              },
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "ul",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Size modifier = 2d6"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Height = 5 feet + 10 inches + your size modifier in inches"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Weight in pounds = 270 + (4 x your size modifier)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Speed."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Your base walking speed is 30 feet."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Constructed Resilience."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " You were created to have remarkable fortitude, represented by the following benefits: "
              },
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "ul",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "You have advantage on saving throws against being poisoned, and you have resistance to poison damage."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "You don’t need to eat, drink, or breathe."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "You are immune to disease."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "You don't need to sleep, and magic can't put you to sleep."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sentry's Rest."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " When you take a long rest, you must spend at least six hours in an inactive, motionless state, rather than sleeping. In this state, you appear inert, but it doesn’t render you unconscious, and you can see and hear as normal."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "element",
        "tag": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "element",
            "tag": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Integrated Protection."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Your body has built-in defensive layers, which can be enhanced with armor. "
              },
              {
                "type": "element",
                "tag": "ul",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "You gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "You can don only armor with which you have proficiency. To don armor, you must incorporate it into your body over the course of 1 hour, during which you must remain in contact with the armor. To doff armor, you must spend 1 hour removing it. You can rest while donning or doffing armor in this way."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "element",
                    "tag": "li",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "While you live, your armor can't be removed from your body against your will."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
